1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with image-based correction of distortions in microscopy section series, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses a method for processing large volumes of microscopy data, which is a common problem in multimedia applications. 
3. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper involves the use of numerical methods to correct for thickness variation in microscopy section series. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the use of discrete mathematics to model and correct for distortions in microscopy section series. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper involves the use of graphics techniques to visualize and analyze microscopy data.
